features: [Farmhouse Kitchen Utensil Holder] Designed with ridged texture with farmhouse style hues, this utensil holder looks just modern & elegant standing on your kitchen counter, fits into your kitchen well

[Large Utensil Holder] With a 6.2” width and 7.2” height hence enough space for storage, 10 to 15 pieces of common utensils can easily go into it, make utensils organized and easy to find, give you a neat and tidy kitchen
[Cork Mat at the Bottom] A non-slip cork mat attached at the bottom, protects your kitchen surfaces from scratch, prevents slipping, avoids noise caused by friction

[Stable & Durable Utensil Crock] Made of premium ceramics, this ceramic utensil holder is clearly heavier than ones made of other materials, steadily stands on your countertop; Glossy glaze & durable material, withstands long-time daily uses

[Not Just a Cooking Utensil Holder] it can be used not only as a spatula spoon cutlery holder, kitchen utensil organizer, but also to hold any other items you can or can’t imagine - paintbrushes, candies, fruits etc. and even act as an ice bucket, a planter, a vase, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and easy to clean
reviews.reviewText: We use this on our kitchen counter for bulky items that won't fit in our kitchen drawers. It is larger than it looks and heavier too. It won't tip over if you fill it with a ton of kitchen items. The color is a warmish light cream, with hint of beige , fairly neutral in most kitchens unless you have the bright white/cool gray theme going. Easy to clean, low maintenance item. I also like the protective bottom so it won't scratch counters if you slide it. A good replacement for what we needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Large holder that looks classic
reviews.reviewText: I have a white cabinet, black counter kitchen. I try to mix color in but I also like to keep that farmhouse feel by adding whites and blacks. This holder is large and holds a ton of stuff. It looks great and seems to be made well. I'm constantly using these utensils so I'm hoping this holds up for the long haul but I think it will.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars And just like that our counter looks better
reviews.reviewText: There's a silent war being waged in my kitchen. Both my husband and I switch off on cooking dinner and we both have strong, polar opposite, opinions about where cooking utensils are stored. This large crock saved our (cooking) relationship. The ridged white porcelain and oversized mouth were exactly what we needed. For him all of the cooking utensils could fit in and we could place the crock by the stove so it was visible while cooking. For me, I love how the crock is another notes of "rustic" charm tying our kitchen together in an aesthetically pleasing way.

reviews.reviewText: My utensil drawer was getting a little full so I needed something that would still match the kitchen (which meant no colorful patterns, etc.) I put the most-used of our cooking utensils in it and there’s still room. I might use the space I saved in the drawer for spices.
